//---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
// Description Essentially just like setting a "soft" breakpoint with the IDE though via
//             an explicit script call.  Pauses execution of game, converts all the
//             objects passed as arguments into a message string and prints it out and
//             breaks at the call point in the IDE or asserts if the runtime is not
//             connected to the IDE.
//             If no arguments are passed then "Debug->Continue to resume..." is used as
//             a default.
// Examples    Debug.break("Got to this point in script on actor ", name)
// See Also    print(), println()
// Author(s)   Conan Reis
//---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

({Object} objs_as_strs)

